{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"language":"python","display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.12","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":14857011,"datasetId":9503470,"databundleVersionId":15717814}],"dockerImageVersionId":31259,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"source":"<a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/code/himanimalhotra/subscription-analytics-retention-ltv-rfm-tableau?scriptVersionId=301281325\" target=\"_blank\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Kaggle\" title=\"Open in Kaggle\" src=\"https://kaggle.com/static/images/open-in-kaggle.svg\"></a>","metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown"},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# **Subscription Analytics Dashboard** \n## Retention, Cohort, Churn & LTV Analysis in Tableau","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Project Overview\n\nFor any SaaS Subscription-based digital product business, high-value retention is the primary growth engine. But when retention fluctuates, and acquisition costs climb, the \"why\" behind user churn often remains a mystery.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Project Objective\n\nI built this SaaS Analytics Dashboard to simulate a real SaaS product analytics scenario, bridge the gap between raw data and strategic action, and analyze user lifecycle from acquisition → activation → retention → revenue stages.\n\n### With Key Features: \n**Retention Visibility**: Clear, cohort-based views of user longevity.\n\n**Revenue Quality**: Deep dives into LTV distribution to identify where real value lives.\n\n**Growth Levers**: Identifying precisely where to optimize the lifecycle for maximum impact.\n\nInstead of just reporting metrics, I approached this from a product decision-making lens — focusing on lifecycle behavior, engagement signals, and revenue impact to identify conversion bottlenecks, optimize retention, and improve customer lifetime value (LTV) and enable product and growth teams to take actionable steps.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Tableau Live Dashboard:\nhttps://public.tableau.com/app/profile/himani.malhotra/viz/ProductAnalyticsSubscriptionRetentionChurnLTVDashboard/ExecutiveOverview","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Business Challenge and What I Analyzed\n\nSubscription businesses rely heavily on customer retention for sustainable growth. While acquisition drives user inflow, long-term profitability depends on minimizing churn and maximizing customer lifetime value (LTV). \n\nThe company lacked clarity on retention trends, cohort performance, churn timing, and revenue contributions across the lifecycle.\n\n**This project analyzes:**\n\n• Cohort retention trends to understand long-term engagement\n\n• Churn drivers by acquisition channel and subscription plan\n\n• Customer Lifetime Value (LTV) optimization by segment\n\n• Revenue Concentration and retention drop-offs\n\n• Subscription funnel from Signup → Subscription → Retention\n\n• RFM segmentation (Recency, Frequency, Monetary) to identify:\n\nChampions\n\nLoyal users\n\nAt-risk customers\n\nLost users","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Key KPIs Tracked\n\n#### Retention Rate\n\n% of users still active after specific time intervals (30, 60, 90 days).\n\n#### Churn Rate\n\n% of users who discontinued subscription within a given period.\n\n#### Customer Lifetime Value (LTV)\n\nTotal revenue generated by a user over their subscription period.\n\n#### Average Revenue Per User (ARPU)\n\n#### Cohort-based Retention\n\nUser retention grouped by subscription start month.\n\n#### User Lifetime\n\nTime Interval in which users remain active on a platform or service before churning\n\n#### Avg Subscription Duration\n\nAverage time a customer remains subscribed before cancelling\n\n#### DAU, MAU, Stickiness\n\nDaily Active Users / Monthly Active Users\n\nStickiness Benchmark:\n\n• 20% = Moderate     \n• 30%+ = Strong             \n• 50%+ = Habit-forming product\n\n#### TTV\n\nTime to Value\n\n#### Activation Rate (Onboarding Success)\n\n% of users who complete a key action within first X days.\n\nLow activation → onboarding friction or unclear value proposition.\n\n#### Feature Adoption Rate\n\n% of users using a core feature.\n\n#### MRR\n\nMonthly Recurring Revenue","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 📂 Dataset Description\n\nThe dataset contains 4 tables:\n\n\n| Tables                         | Attributes                                                                                                            |\n| -------------------------------| ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| **1. Users**                   | User acquisition information                                                                                          |\n|                                | User_ID, Signup_Date, Acquisition_Channel, Country, Device                                                            |\n| **2. Subscriptions**           | Tracks subscription lifecycle                                                                                         |\n|                                | Subscription_ID, Plan_Type (Basic, Standard, Premium), Start_Date, End_Date, Monthly_Price, Status (Active / Churned) |                                                                                     \n| **3. Payments**                | Tracks recurring subscription payments                                                                                |\n|                                | Payment_ID, Payment_Date, Revenue                                                                                     |\n| **4. Activity**                | Tracks product usage                                                                                                  | \n|                                | Activity_Date, Sessions, Feature_Used                                                                                 |\n\n---","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Analytical Approach\n\n### 1️⃣ Data Preparation\nRemoved duplicates\n\nCleaned subscription lifecycle data\n\nCreated churn flags (Active vs Churned)\n\nEngineered retention buckets\n\nDerived cohort month\n\n### 2️⃣ Feature Engineering\nLTV per customer\n\nRetention percentage calculations(30/60/90)\n\nCohort indexing\n\nRevenue segmentation\n\n### 3️⃣ Dashboard Development (Tableau)\nExecutive Overview Page\n\nCohort Retention Heatmap\n\nChurn Trend Analysis\n\nLTV Distribution Histogram\n\nInteractive filters (Plan, Acquisition Channel, User Country, Device Type)","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Analysis Framework\n\n### 1️⃣ Funnel Analysis\nSignup → Subscription → Retention\n\nIdentified conversion friction and drop-off percentages.\n\n### 2️⃣ Cohort Retention Analysis\nTracked retention trends by signup month.\n\nUsed to evaluate product stickiness and engagement decay.\n\n### 3️⃣ Activation & Stickiness\nMeasured:\n\nActivation Rate (within 7 days)\n\nDAU / MAU ratio\n\nTime to Value\n\n### 4️⃣ Revenue & LTV Analysis\nARPU calculation\n\nLTV distribution\n\nRevenue contribution by segment\n\n### 5️⃣ RFM Segmentation\nSegmented users into:\n\nChampions\n\nLoyal Customers\n\nAt-Risk Users\n\nLow-Value Users","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Dashboard Structure","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Executive Overview Dashboard \n\n👉 Designed for leadership-level quick insights.\nHigh-level business health summary\n\n**KPIs:**\n\n*Total Users* : COUNTD([User_ID])\n\n*Active Subscribers* : COUNTD(IF [Status] = \"Active\" THEN [User_ID] END)\n\n*Total Revenue* : SUM([Revenue])\n\n*Churn Rate %* : COUNTD(IF [Status]=\"Churned\" THEN [User_ID] END)/COUNTD([User_ID])\n\n*Average LTV* : SUM([Revenue]) / COUNTD([User_ID])\n\n**Charts:**\n\n*Monthly Active Users trend*\n\n*Revenue Trend Over Time*","metadata":{},"attachments":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Growth & Acquisition Analysis\n\n*Active vs Churned User Subscription Trend*\n\n*Channel Performance*\n\n*LTV Growth*\n\n***Subscription Funnel: Signup → Subscriber → Paying User → Repeat Subscriber***","metadata":{},"attachments":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Cohort Retention Analysis\n\n*Monthly cohort heatmap*\n\n*Retention Trend by Signup Month*\n\n*Retention drop-off patterns*\n\n","metadata":{},"attachments":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Retention & Churn Analysis\n*Churn rate by Plan*\n\n*Churn rate by Acquisition Channel*\n\n*Monthly Churn Trend*\n\n*Retention Rate*\n\n","metadata":{},"attachments":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## LTV Analysis\n*LTV by Channel*\n\n*LTV by Plan*\n\n*Channel-level LTV Comparison*\n\n*30 / 60 / 90 Day Retention*\n\n","metadata":{},"attachments":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## RFM Segmentation\n\n### Recency, Frequency, Monetary fields.\n\n**1. Recency (Days since last payment)**\n\nDATEDIFF('day',\n{ FIXED [User_ID]: MAX([Payment_Date]) },\nTODAY()\n)\n\nLower value = more recent = better user\n\n**2. Frequency (Total number of payments)**\n\n{ FIXED [User_ID]: COUNT([Payment_ID]) }\n\nHigher = more loyal\n\n**3. Monetary (Total revenue per user)**\n\n{ FIXED [User_ID]: SUM([Revenue]) }\n\nHigher = more valuable user\n\n### RFM Scores (1–5)\n\n**Recency Score**\n\nIF [Recency] <= 30 THEN 5\nELSEIF [Recency] <= 60 THEN 4\nELSEIF [Recency] <= 120 THEN 3\nELSEIF [Recency] <= 180 THEN 2\nELSE 1\nEND\n\n**Frequency Score**\n\nIF [Frequency] >= 12 THEN 5\nELSEIF [Frequency] >= 9 THEN 4\nELSEIF [Frequency] >= 6 THEN 3\nELSEIF [Frequency] >= 3 THEN 2\nELSE 1\nEND\n\n**Monetary Score**\n\nIF [Monetary] >= 300 THEN 5\nELSEIF [Monetary] >= 200 THEN 4\nELSEIF [Monetary] >= 100 THEN 3\nELSEIF [Monetary] >= 50 THEN 2\nELSE 1\nEND\n\n### Combined RFM Score\n\nSTR([Recency Score])\n+\nSTR([Frequency Score])\n+\nSTR([Monetary Score])\n\n555 = Best customer,111 = Worst customer\n\n### Customer Segments\n\nIF [Recency Score]>=4 AND [Frequency Score]>=4 AND [Monetary Score]>=4 THEN \"Champions\"\n\nELSEIF [Frequency Score]>=4 AND [Monetary Score]>=4 THEN \"Loyal Customers\"\n\nELSEIF [Recency Score]>=4 AND [Frequency Score]<=2 THEN \"New Customers\"\n\nELSEIF [Recency Score]<=2 AND [Frequency Score]>=3 THEN \"At Risk\"\n\nELSEIF [Recency Score]<=2 AND [Frequency Score]<=2 THEN \"Lost Customers\"\n\nELSE \"Average Customers\"\nEND\n\n\n","metadata":{},"attachments":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Engagement & Conversion Analysis\n*Time to Value*\n\n*Stickiness*\n\n*User Lifetime Distribution (Days)*:\n\n30-Day = Activation success\n\n60-Day = Value reinforcement\n\n90-Day = Habit formation\n\n*Expansion Rate (Premium Plan)*\n\n*Feature Adoption Rate*\n\n*Engagement vs Retention*","metadata":{},"attachments":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Filter on all pages by Plan Type, User Country, User Device and Acquisition Channel","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Key Product Insights\n\n### 1. Retention Drop After 60 Days\nRetention is strong for 30 days, but drops significantly between 60 and 90 days. Users who survive past the third billing cycle tend to stabilize, marking this as the critical activation window\n\nImplication: Onboarding, activation & engagement improvements can drastically impact retention.\n\n### 2. Cohort Quality Varies\nSome acquisition cohorts show weaker long-term retention — suggesting differences in channel quality.\n\nImplication: Possible product-market fit or onboarding experience issue.\n\n### 3. Revenue is Highly Concentrated\nPremium plan users and the \"Champion\" segment (top 20% of users) drive the vast majority of total revenue\n\nImplication: Growth strategy should balance acquisition + lifecycle optimization.\n\n### 4. LTV Distribution is Right-Skewed\nPremium plan users generated significantly higher lifetime value\n\nHigh acquisition ≠ High retention — paid channels drove volume/acquisition but lower LTV/retention.\n\nImplication: Invest in engagement loops, loyalty benefits, and renewal incentives.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Strategic Business Recommendations\n\n### 1. Strengthen 30–60 Day Engagement\nTrigger behavioral nudges\n\nIntroduce feature discovery emails\n\nGuided Onboarding to improve First 30-Day Experience\n\nIncentivize milestone usage\n\n### 2. Protect High LTV Segment\nImplement an early churn prediction model\n\nPremium annual renewal incentives, loyalty benefits, and Plan upgrades with bundled features\n\nDedicated retention campaigns\n\n### 3. Improve Acquisition Quality\nReassess channels tied to weak cohorts\n\nAlign acquisition with long-term value\n\n### 4. Introduce Proactive Churn Alerts\nFlag users inactive for X days, add Usage drop signals, and Payment failure tracking \n\nOffer upgrade or discount incentives","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Expected Business Impact\n\nIf implemented, projected outcomes include:\n\n+5–8% increase in 60-day retention\n\n+10–15% increase in average LTV\n\n3–5% reduction in churn\n\nHigher revenue stability\n\nEven a small retention lift in subscription models creates disproportionate revenue growth.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## What the dashboard covers\n• Executive overview with Revenue, Active Users, LTV, and Churn Rate\n\n• Cohort retention analysis to track user engagement over time\n\n• Churn analysis by acquisition channel and subscription plan\n\n• Customer Lifetime Value (LTV) analysis to identify high-value segments\n\n• RFM segmentation to categorize users into Champions, Loyal, At-Risk, and Lost customers\n\n• Subscription funnel analysis from signup to repeat subscription","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Product Implications:\n• Better marketing budget allocation to optimize revenue growth\n\n• Build nudges for declining engagement users - High-value user targeting\n\n• Improve onboarding experience during the first 30 days to reduce Churn\n\n• Optimize marketing spend toward high-LTV acquisition channels - Target campaigns toward high-monetary, low-recency users\n\n• Identification of high-value user segments","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## What This Project Demonstrates\n✔ Strong product analytics fundamentals\n\n✔ Deep understanding of retention economics\n\n✔ Cohort-based thinking\n\n✔ Revenue-centric analysis\n\n✔ Business storytelling with data\n\n✔ BI Dashboard design for decision-makers","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Learning\nThis project strengthened my ability to connect user behavior to business impact and think beyond dashboards toward product decisions.\n\nOpen to feedback and product analytics opportunities!","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Author\n\n### Himani Malhotra\n\n#### Data & Product Analyst\n\nmalhotrahimani29@gmail.com\n\n[GitHub](https://github.com/himanimalhotra17/Business-Data-Analysis-Portfolio) ","metadata":{}}]}